  <h2>Philosophy of Science:</h2>
  <h2>An Overview for Cognitive Science </h2>
  <p>William Bechtel</p>
  <p>Hillsdale, NJ: Lawrence Erlbaum Associates, 1988</p>
  <p align="left">Chapters with links are now available on the web. A more recent treatment of the topics in chapters 5 and 6 can be found in Bechtel, W. and Hamilton, A. 2007). <a href="bechtel.hamilton.reduction.pdf">Reductionism, integration, and the unity of the sciences</a>. T. Kuipers (ed.), <em>Philosophy of Science: Focal Issues</em> (Volume 1 of the Handbook of the Philosophy of Science). New York: Elsevier.</p>
